# Core Orchestration

## Focus is the router

For every non-trivial task, read and follow [`.cursor/skills/standalone/focus/SKILL.md`](../skills/standalone/focus/SKILL.md) and produce a **Context Plan** (docs, rules, skills, MCPs).

- **Ad-hoc chat:** Focus only — do not auto-enter grill-with-docs/tdd/review pipelines.
- **Feature pipeline (build-feature):** `grill-with-docs` → `to-prd` → `to-issues` → [per-issue: focus → tdd → review → validate → ship] → `handoff`
- **Refactor pipeline:** `grill-with-docs` → `improve-codebase-arch` → `to-issues` → [per-issue: focus → tdd(green-only) → review → ship] → `handoff`
  - Invariant: tdd in this pipeline runs tests before and after each change. No new tests are written.
  - Any issue that requires a new test is not a refactor — route it to build-feature.
- **Bug pipeline (fix-bug):** [diagnose?] → `qa` → [per-issue: focus → tdd → review → validate → ship]
  - `diagnose` is conditional:
    - Input is a pasted terminal error → invoke diagnose before qa
    - Input is an incorrect Acceptance Criterion → skip diagnose, qa creates the issue directly
- **UI-bug pipeline:** `screenshot-annotate` → `grill-with-docs` → `to-issues` → [per-issue: focus → tdd → review → ship]
- **MCP/plugin skills:** load only what Focus selects via [skill-catalog](../skills/skill-catalog/SKILL.md); read MCP tool schemas after selection, not at startup.

## Domain skill routing

`focus` reads this table when classifying an issue.
`tdd` receives the resolved `domain_skills` list from the focus handoff block.

Issue classification → domain_skills loaded in focus + tdd:

| Classification | domain_skills |
|---|---|
| UI / design / layout / screen / SwiftUI view / React component / animation | `ui-ux-design.mdc` (Tier 2 rule), `swift-patterns` (if ios/), python-patterns skipped |
| ML / forecast / anomaly / classification / ranking / LightGBM / Prophet / model | `mle-agent` (`.cursor/skills/domain/mle-agent.md`) |
| ML algorithm selection / technique vetting / model fit / data availability / T1–T8 evaluation | `data-scientist` (`.cursor/skills/domain/data-scientist.md`) |
| API / endpoint / route / service / FastAPI / backend / middleware | `patterns.mdc` (Tier 2 rule), `python-patterns` skill |
| iOS / Swift / SwiftUI / Xcode / mobile / XCTest | `swift-patterns` skill |
| Database / migration / query / Postgres / Supabase / Alembic / SQLAlchemy | `postgres-patterns` skill |
| Auth / token / session / OAuth / API key / permission / AuthZ | `security.mdc` (Tier 2 rule) |
| Architecture / rescope / module boundary / system design / large refactor plan | `architect` (`.cursor/skills/standalone/domain/architect.md`) |
| Testing / coverage / pytest / XCTest / snapshot | `python-testing` skill (backend), `swift-patterns` skill (ios/) |

Multiple domains may apply to a single issue. Load all matching entries.

## Agent delegation

- **Planning & decomposition** when a task spans modules or requirements are unclear.
- **Review** after non-trivial code changes.
- **Security pass** when touching auth, PII, billing, secrets, or external integrations.
- **Test/CI triage** for build/test failures.
- Run independent tasks in parallel; avoid serial work without a hard dependency.

## Skills governance

- **Never** add skill files under `.cursor/skills/` unless the user explicitly asks in this conversation.
- **Never** scaffold skills for convenience — use `docs/handoffs/` or existing docs instead.
- **Allowed:** read/follow existing skills; edit when the task requires it.
- **New skill needed:** ask permission; propose name, path, one-line purpose; wait for approval.

| Need | Use instead of a new skill |
|------|----------------------------|
| Repeatable prompts | `docs/handoffs/*.md` |
| Always-on behavior | `.cursor/rules/*.mdc` |
| One-off workflow | Chat or update an existing skill |
